<DOC><DOCNO> AP901115-0116 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-11-15-90 1612EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-Newspage-Alydar'sDeat     11-15 0183</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Newspage-Alydar's Death,0195</SECOND><HEAD>Alydar, Runnerup in Memorable Triple Crown Races, Destroyed</HEAD><DATELINE>LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Alydar the horse that ran second toAffirmed in memorable 1978 Triple Crown races and became aninfluential sire, was destroyed Thursday at Calumet Farms afterbreaking his injured right leg.   The 15-year-old Alydar, who sired such champions as Alysheba,Easy Goer and Turkoman, kicked his stall door late Tuesday andunderwent surgery Wednesday.   Dr. Larry Bramlage, who helped operate on the chestnut stallion,said Thursday: ``It was either maintain him in a tranquilized state... or wean him out of the sling. Fifteen minutes after it was off,he slipped and fell, breaking his right femur.''   The second injury was to the same leg.   The horse was buried at the farm, where he had stood at studsince 1979.   Alydar and Affirmed began their epic duel in their 2-year-oldseason and the rivalry culminated in the Kentucky Derby, Preaknessand Belmont Stakes. Affirmed won all three races by a total of lessthan three lengths.   Alydar had quite a few notable victories, including the FloridaDerby, Blue Grass Stakes and Arlington Stakes.</TEXT></DOC>